dcterms:creator: P. Erdős

dcterms:description: Erdős–Rényi (ER) graphs are random graphs where each edge is included in the graph with a probability p independent from every other edge.
dcterms:title: Erdős–Rényi (ER) Graphs

dcterms:creator: R. Albert
A.-L. Barabási
dcterms:description: Barabási–Albert (BA) graphs are scale-free networks generated by a preferential attachment mechanism, where new nodes are more likely to connect to already well-connected nodes.
dcterms:title: Barabási–Albert (BA) Graphs

dcterms:description: Power-law tree models are used to represent networks where the degree distribution follows a power law, often used in modeling hierarchical structures.
dcterms:title: Power-law Tree Models

dcterms:description: Star graphs are a type of graph where one central node is connected to all other nodes, which are not connected to each other.
dcterms:title: Star Graph

dcterms:description: Wireless network simulation data used for training graph convolutional networks (GCNs) in the context of scheduling in wireless networks.
dcterms:title: Wireless Network Simulation Data (for GCN training)
